APPELL, Appellant, v. STEMMLER, Respondent. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. March 7, 1894.) Appeal from eighth district court. Action by Jacob Appell against Theodore W. Stemmier.

Argued before DALY, C. J., and PRYOR, J.

A. J. Appell, for appellant. Douglass & Minton, for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment reversed, new trial ordered, costs to appellant to abide event.
